description: As the answers for their missing father begin to unfold, Iya tries her best to talk Marit out of her dangerous search for him. Meanwhile, Daggy does his best to talk Elisa out of her date with the dimwitted Derek. Plus: What happens when Christa gets hit on in the middle of an STD clinic? All we can say is feel pity for the poor sucker (He’s gonna need it!) Tragically sad…irresistibly funny… the story of four half-sisters with one remarkable past continues! 32 pages!

A flashback of the girls when they first came together as a family reveals pieces of who they once were. Meanwhile in the present, Iyas depression begins to surface while Christa is in rare sarcastic form when Elisa asks her for dating advice (Let’s just say the poor sucker never had a chance.) Also in this issue: The debut of Uncle. 32 pages!

Christa is busted by Trevor (the clinic guy's) sister while the reason for Elisa's "date from Hell" is finally revealed (You're not gonna believe it!). Plus: the first appearance of Highball!!! See why reviewers call Fade "one of the most wonderfully written comics on the stands!" 32 pages!

Things heat up as Marit has her first bloody confrontation with Highball and the family begins to fall apart under the pressure. Plus: If you thought you knew Elisa, think again! You'll see a side of her you never thought existed in a story we could only call "written promises…spoken lies!" 32 pages!

The EISNER-NOMINATED team of Murphy and Dalrymple are bringing the first chapter of Fade From Blue to a fast-paced conclusion! In this issue, Marit comes face to face with the man that killed her mother. Plus: Tensions mount as the girls struggle to pack up their lives and leave home one last time. See why Wizard calls Fade one of this years “Buzz Books” for 2003! 32 pg.

The EISNER-NOMINATED team of Murphy and Dalrymple present the final chapter of the 10-issue series. Is Uncle a traitor? What’s Iya doing on a ledge? Where will you be when Dag admits his love to Elisa? And, the mother of all endings: Is Marit insane?!? Trust us, you’ll never guess the ending of this long-awaited, ready to win another Eisner, series-end shocker!!! 48pg.

The best-selling 12-issue series illustrated by Alex Ross is now available as a single volume hardcover at DC's standard trim size. The villains of the Legion of Doom - led by Lex Luthor and Brainiac - band together to save the world after a shared dream that seems to be a vision of the Earth's demise. They are confronted by the Justice League of America, who doubt their motives - and as their true plans unfold the two teams do battle.

description:
How do you trust someone when you no longer know yourself?

David Barrot, a retired Corrections Officer, moved to Grey Oaks after the tragic death of his son, Cale. He bought a farm on the outskirts of town with his wife Lucy and daughter Jessie to begin life anew, putting aside the dark events of their past. Unfortunately for them, the dark just won't leave David alone. The first sightings started months ago, igniting rumors of disease and infection. Newspaper stories of strange side effects and mysterious lesions appearing on livestock spread quickly. Perhaps it was inevitable that the people of Grey Oaks would be next.

These are their Changing Ways.

Based on the Western character created by legendary short story writer O. Henry in his 1907 short story "The Caballero's Way," The Cisco Kid starred in a comic strip that ran for fifteen years. Volume One reprints this classic American comic strip by Rod Reed and Jose Luis Salinas from its beginning on January 15, 1951 to January 31, 1953 with an introduction by Sergio Aragonés, rarely seen Salinas artwork, biographical information, and more!
name: Vol. 1: 1951-1953

description:
Beloved Rival

My heart ached for them both... Mary Hagers, who was dying, and Bart, her husband, hose heart was breaking as the end neared! I could only stand by, making Mary's end as painless as possible... pitying Bart whom I had learned to love!

Imperfect Love

Like any other woman in love, I thought my man was the most talented male in the world! But I was different... with my mother's help, I was going to see that he reached the top! With my mother's help, I almost destroyed Stan's love for me, the only thing that meany anything!

Pull of the Past (Text Only Story)

The Too Trusting Heart

I'd only gone out a few times with Carl Linden but I knew I loved him as I never would love again! I knew that others thought Carl wanted only my money, not my love... but Carl was welcome to both!

A Lesson In Heartbreak

The setting was perfect... there was a full moon. I wore my most enticing perfume... and Russ Peyton held me in his arms! It was time for a small town romeo to learn... A Lesson In Heartbreak

Vacation Manhunt

It was to be a glorious, exciting two weeks... my summer vacation... but I had an ulterior motive.. yes! To meet the right man! Man, meaning: M... oney, at... tractive, n... ice! But I almost forgot that I was the bait in this manhunt!

description: The New Avengers are about to face their biggest threat: the revitalized, resurrected and rejuvenated H.A.M.M.E.R. - led by none other than Norman Osborn! What insanity is Osborn about to unleash on the world? And can the Avengers stop his master plan when Osborn unleashes a new squad of Dark Avengers?! Get ready for old-school blockbuster action as the New Avengers' new lineup charges into action! And wait until you find out who's behind the Dark Avengers' masks! (Actually, wait until the Avengers find out!) As the blistering battle rages, an Avenger leaves the team in defeat, a Dark Avenger just might become a New Avenger, and not everyone makes it out alive! Collecting NEW AVENGERS (2010) #16.1 and #17-23.

description: It's a new start for the Academy kids! New students! New staff! New West Coast campus! But when a classic Avenger is murdered, everyone becomes a suspect - and guest-stars Captain America, Luke Cage and Hawkeye brawl with the student body?! As student turns on student, and students clash with staff, which cast members are trying to shut down the Academy? It's a surprise revelation that will have your jaw on the floor! Plus: Reptil's darkest secret is revealed! And when X-23 joins Avengers Academy, will they survive the experience? Collecting AVENGERS ACADEMY #21-26.
